  <static seed="102" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionSubtractionWordProblems50.pg">
    <statement><p>Sarah and Parnell are sharing a pizza. Sarah ate <m>{{\frac{3}{8}}}</m> of the pizza, and Parnell ate <m>{{\frac{3}{10}}}</m> of the pizza. How much more pizza did Sarah eat than Parnell?</p>
<p>Sarah ate <fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/> more of the pizza than Parnell ate.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{3}{40}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To find the difference of two numbers, we use subtraction:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{3}{8}}} - {{\frac{3}{10}}} 
      \amp = \frac{3 \cdot 5}{8 \cdot 5}-\frac{3 \cdot 4}{10 \cdot 4} \\
      \amp = \frac{15}{40} - \frac{12}{40} \\
      \amp = \frac{15-12}{40} \\
      
      \amp = {{\frac{3}{40}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Sarah ate <m>{{\frac{3}{40}}}</m> more of the pizza than Parnell ate.</p>
</solution>
